result.execSummary:
The defendant Taylor R Peterson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property >$10,000 [Modifiers: Repeater, PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Taylor R Peterson in court with attorney Michael Scholke.  Defendant Taylor R Peterson in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 1:00 PM. Called 15CF168 and 15CF134. Court - according to plea questionnaire - the defendant will be pleading G to count #3 on 15CF134 and on 15CF168 - pleading G  to only count. State and Scholke and Peterson agree. State - parties will be free to argue sentence - there will be other counts dismissed and read in, counts #1, #2, #4 and #5 on 15CF134. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. sholke informs Court that the repeater allegation in 15CF134 is being dismissed. State agrees. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - on 15CF168 - recommends 6 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of initial confinement followed by 3 years of ES - concurrent to anything he is currently serving; on 15CF134 - recommends 10 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 5 years of initial confinement followed by 5 years of ES - concurrent to his existing sentence. State has complied with victim notification requirements - no restitution requested. Scholke makes final argument prior to sentencing - recommends running everything concurrent to current sentence and asking the Court to not impose additional year of incarceration.Peterson makes statement, remorseful. Court dismisses and reads in counts #1, #2, #4 and #5 on 15CF134. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 15CF168 - count #1 - 6 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of initial confinement followed by 3 years of ES - concurrent to current sentence; 15CF134 - 10 years in WI State Prison System consisting of 5 years of initial confinement followed by 5 years of ES - concurrent to current sentence, conditions of ES include: costs on each count - paid thru ES, submit DNA sample with surcharge assessed, not eligible for programs, no possession of firearms, no voting rights, right to appeal, adjourned.
Final pre-trial on June 30, 2016 at 01:00 pm.
